 BOOL CALLBACK MyDlgProc(HWND hDlg, UINT msg, WPARAM wParam, LPARAM lParam)
 {
    switch(msg)
    {
        case WM_INITDIALOG:
            return TRUE;
        case WM_DESTROY:
            EndDialog(hDlg, 0);
            return TRUE;
    }
    return FALSE;
 }

Is the case statement supposed to fall through to the next case, or is this simply false laziness? [[User:Puckdropper|Puckdropper]] ([[User talk:Puckdropper|talk]]) 22:59, 12 December 2007 (UTC)

: Never mind, when the program hits the return statement it won't go to the next case.  I'd probably use a break; anyway, but that's just a style issue.  [[User:Puckdropper|Puckdropper]] ([[User talk:Puckdropper|talk]]) 01:40, 15 December 2007 (UTC)

