{{WikiProject Languages|spanish=yes}}
==Palabrito== In the "A Few Important Words" section, the table said "Palabritos - Little words". But surely it'd be "palabritas", since "palabra" ends with "a"? I went ahead and changed it, but I wonder if there might be a better term. - [[User:Furrykef|Furrykef]] ([[User talk:Furrykef|talk]]) 08:19, 16 December 2007 (UTC) : Yes, you're right. I make hundreds of errors, typographical and otherwise, so thank you for noticing and correcting them. Regards, &mdash;[[User:Celestianpower|Cel<font color="green">es</font>tianpower]] <sup>[[user talk:Celestianpower|háblame]]</sup> 17:00, 16 December 2007 (UTC)
==Albañil/constructor== My dictionaries all suggest that "constructor" refers to a firm, and "albañil" refers to a person, so I changed "constructor(a)" to "albañil". I'm far from a native speaker, though, so I'm posting here to make sure that this is a good idea... - [[User:Furrykef|Furrykef]] ([[User talk:Furrykef|talk]]) 08:19, 16 December 2007 (UTC) : Hmm. Well, we learnt it wrong at school :P. Thanks! &mdash;[[User:Celestianpower|Cel<font color="green">es</font>tianpower]] <sup>[[user talk:Celestianpower|háblame]]</sup> 17:00, 16 December 2007 (UTC)

