{{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic| name=Confringo| type=[[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic#Spells|Spell]] (Curse)| features=Makes a thing explode| appearance=[[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Books/Deathly Hallows|''Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows'']]}}
== Overview ==
'''''Confringo''''' is a spell or curse used to make things explode.
== Extended Description ==
{{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Beginner Spoiler}}
As [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Harry Potter|Harry]] is making his escape from [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Places/Privet Drive|the Dursleys']] during the fourth chapter (The Seven Potters) of the [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Books/Deathly Hallows|''Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows'']], the side car that has been bolted on to [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Sirius Black|Sirius']] flying motorbike, in which Harry is riding, breaks away due to the strain of flight. Harry is rescued by [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Rubeus Hagrid|Hagrid]], but then uses this spell to destroy the abandoned side car, disabling one of the attacking Death Eaters with the fragments.
This spell is used again in the battle with [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Nagini|Nagini]]; here, [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Hermione Granger|Hermione]] casts it, and it ricochets around the room before hitting something it can blow up. Hermione later identifies it as the Blasting Curse.
== Analysis ==
This is similar in effect to a differently-named spell used in some fan fiction; one may wonder whether the name was chosen specifically to avoid similarity to the name in the fan fiction. It also appears similar in effect to the [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic/Expulso|Expulso]] and [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic/Deprimo|Deprimo]] spells.
== Questions == {{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Questions}}
== Greater Picture ==
{{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Intermediate Spoiler}}
[[Category:Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter]]

{{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic| name=Decoy Detonator| type=Magical Device| features=Creates a distraction| appearance=[[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Books/Half-Blood Prince|''Harry Potter and the Half-Blood Prince'']]}}
== Overview ==
'''''Decoy Detonators''''' are products of [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Places/Weasleys' Wizard Wheezes|Weasleys' Wizard Wheezes]]. They are small devices which scurry off into shadows and then make a noise, thus decoying people away.
== Extended Description ==
{{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Beginner Spoiler}}
We first see Decoy Detonators when [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Harry Potter|Harry]], [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Ron Weasley|Ron]], [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Ginny Weasley|Ginny]], and [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Hermione Granger|Hermione]], along with [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Arthur Weasley|Mr.]] and [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Molly Weasley|Mrs. Weasley]], visit [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Fred and George Weasley|the Twins']] new joke shop in [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Places/Diagon Alley|Diagon Alley]]. Fred, giving Harry the tour of the shop, takes him into the back room where the more serious magical items are kept, and there shows him the Decoy Detonators, saying they can't keep them on the shelves.
When the Trio are planning to break into the Ministry in [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Books/Deathly Hallows/Chapter 12|''Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows'']], Decoy Detonators are one of the things on Hermione's list. Harry then uses one of them to distract a room full of witches and wizards so that he can enter [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Dolores Umbridge|Umbridge]]'s office undetected. The Detonator scuttles silently to the far side of the room, then blows itself up, making a sharp noise and a cloud of smoke. The witches and wizards examine it for a long time, finally deciding that it is an escapee from the department of Experimental Charms.
== Analysis ==
== Questions == {{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Questions}}
== Greater Picture ==
{{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Intermediate Spoiler}}
