'''Edmeston, New York (Businesses)'''
==The Gaskin House==
Between [[History of Edmeston, New York/1840s#1840|1840]] and [[History of Edmeston, New York/1840s#1843|1843]], [[History of Edmeston, New York/People#P|S. H. Preston]] built the second hotel in town at the location of the current Bank/Post Office building.  Preston bought the land from [[History of Edmeston, New York/People#D|Adin Deming]], the first settler in the area.
