[[w:SmallTalk|Smalltalk]] is an [[w:Object-oriented programming|object-oriented]] programming language developed by [[w:Alan_Kay|Alan Kay]], [[w:Dan_Ingalls|Dan Ingalls]], [[w:Adele_Goldberg|Adel Goldberg]], [[w:Ted_Kaehler|Ted Kaehler]], [[w:Scott_Wallace|Scott Wallace]], and others during the 1970s, influenced by [[w:Lisp|Lisp]], [[w:Logo|Logo]],[[w:Sketchpad|Sketchpad]] and [[w:Simula|Simula]]. It has influenced the design of many languages especially [[w:Objective_C|Objective C]], and [[w:Ruby|Ruby]].


There are many versions of Smalltalk [http://www.smalltalk.org/versions available]. For this book we are going to use [http://www.squeak.org/ Squeak]. First download a version of Squeak appropriate for your platform.

